    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-12-03T13:14:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-12-03T13:14:00-05:00" n="673" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d673">
                <head>No. 671.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Sickles</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-12-03T18:00:00-00:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 3, 1873—6 p.m.</date> (Received 9
                                    p.m.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>President Castelar informs me now that powers have been sent this
                                afternoon to Spanish minister in Washington to negotiate the place,
                                day, and hour of the delivery of the Virginius to United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>SICKLES.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
